Class Strings

java.lang.Object
  fiftyone.mobile.detection.Strings

public class Strings
extends Object

Rather than store a copy of every string held in the data files a list of strings is used and the index of the string is held in the data classes.

Author:

Field Detail

_index

public final SortedMap<Integer,Object> _index
Index containing the hashcode of the string as the index and either the index in the _values list as the value or a list of values that match the hashcode. It is possible for several different values to share the same hashcode.

_values

final List<String> _values
All the strings used in the 51Degrees.mobi file are held in this stack.

add

public int add(String value)
Adds a new string value to the list of strings. If the value already exists then it's index is returned. If it doesn't then a new entry is added.

Parameters:
value - String value to add.
Returns:
Index of the string in the _values list. Used the Get method to retrieve the string value later.

indexOf

private int indexOf(String value,
                    int hashcode)
Gets the index of the value and hashcode. The hashcode is provided to avoid calculating when it already exists from the string.

Parameters:
value - The value who's index is required from the list.
hashcode - The hashcode of the value.
Returns:
The integer index of the string value in the list, otherwise -1.
